commitResults.messageBody:
Task subclasses have some common behaviors.

The common behaviors across different Task subtypes cause code
duplication.

Extracting the common behavior into a super class allows us to use
polymorphism when storing file content.

Let's pull up storage behaviors common to all task subclasses into a new
parent class named Task.

Using inheritance is preferable over composition in this situation
because the common behaviors are not composable.
